The paper deals with the mutual information of wireless channels, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It also involves numerical approximations, which suggests a possible connection to numerical analysis (cs.NA). The use of ergodic and stationary processes in the representation of the channel implies a possible connection to statistical inference (cs.SI). The study of the channel as an operator suggests a possible connection to control theory (cs.SY). Finally, the mention of random matrix theory suggests a possible connection to multimedia (cs.MM), which often involves the use of matrices in data analysis.
